  "productivefrogs.jei.variant_slime.info": "A %1$s. Killed by a %2$s, drops a Froglight stamped with this variant. Use the Slime Milker to convert into a Slime Milk bucket for infinite renewable production.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.variant_froglight.info": "Dropped when a %1$s eats a %2$s. Smelts in a furnace to the resource it represents.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.frog.info": "Eats %1$s variants. When fed a variant Resource Slime (e.g. an Iron Slime), drops a Froglight stamped with that variant. Category-only slimes are intermediates and produce nothing.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.tadpole.info": "Matures into a %1$s while in water.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.frog_egg.info": "Place on water to spawn a Primed Frog Egg block. After a delay, hatches into 1-3 Tadpoles that mature into %1$s.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.primed_egg.info": "Hatches after a delay into 1-3 Tadpoles that mature into %1$s. Must be placed on a water source.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.slime_milk.info": "Place in the world to create a Slime Milk source block. Periodically spawns a %1$s on a solid adjacent block. The output of feeding a variant Slime Bucket into the Slime Milker.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.parent_species.bog.info": "Spawns in swamps and mangrove swamps. Infuse with a variant primer (bone, gunpowder, clay, slime ball, etc.) to convert into a variant Resource Slime that frogs can eat.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.parent_species.cave.info": "Spawns in dripstone caves, deep dark, and lush caves. Infuse with a variant primer (iron ingot, copper ingot, gold ingot, redstone, lapis, coal, diamond, etc.) to convert into a variant Resource Slime.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.parent_species.geode.info": "Spawns in mountain peaks (stony, jagged, frozen) and snowy slopes. Infuse with an emerald (and other geode-themed primers, post-V1.1) to convert into a variant Resource Slime.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.parent_species.tide.info": "Spawns in oceans (deep, warm, lukewarm). Infuse with a prismarine shard or sponge to convert into a variant Resource Slime.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.parent_species.infernal.info": "Spawns in the Nether (nether wastes, basalt deltas, soul sand valley). Infuse with magma cream to convert into a variant Resource Slime.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.parent_species.void.info": "Spawns in the End (outer islands). Infuse with an ender pearl to convert into a variant Resource Slime.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.empty_frog_egg.info": "Bottle a vanilla frogspawn block (right-click with a glass bottle) to fill this. Prime the resulting filled bottle with a variant primer item to assign a species.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.slime_milker.info": "Furnace-style production block. Right-click to open. Place a Slime Bucket containing a variant Resource Slime in the input slot — after 100 ticks, it converts to the matching Slime Milk bucket. Hopper-compatible.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.spawnery.info": "Turns glass bottles into bottled frogspawn, fueled by slime balls (one ball per bottle). Leave the primer slot empty for plain vanilla frogspawn, or add a species primer (iron ingot for Cave, amethyst shard for Geode, bone for Bog, prismarine shard for Tide, blaze powder for Infernal, an ender pearl for Void) to bottle that species' eggs. Off by default; modpacks can retune the primer for each species.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.empty_slime_bucket.info": "Right-click a size-1 Resource Slime to capture it. The bucket records the slime's variant (or species, for category-only slimes) and can be released elsewhere or fed into the Slime Milker.",
  "productivefrogs.jei.empty_tadpole_bucket.info": "Right-click a Resource Tadpole to capture it. The bucket records the tadpole's species and can be released elsewhere — released tadpoles will continue maturing into a Resource Frog.",
